<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in charge of someone • in the charge of someone</xh5><p> <i>in charge of someone—</i>exercising care or supervision of a person: Other people <u>in charge of</u> children, such as teachers or foster carers, do not have parental responsibility.</p><p> <i>in the charge of someone—</i>said of smb. under the care or supervision of a person: She has been <u>in the charge of</u> her grandmother since her mother and father died.</p> </entry>
